{"TopicId":22809,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.12.x] Kerbal Alarm Clock v3.13.0.0 (April 10)","CreatedByName":"TriggerAu","CreatedById":57838,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-04-19T12:01:32Z","PageNum":92,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Stangryn","CreatedById":104351,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-17T18:02:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the update Trigger, I can once again go back to kerbal\u0027ing properly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"BLN","CreatedById":182379,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-17T18:10:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou did a mistake updating the title of the topic. We\u0027re in 2018 now \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0 \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57838-triggerau/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257838\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57838-triggerau/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@TriggerAu\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThanks for the update !\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"maculator","CreatedById":122127,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-17T18:20:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223325472\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002222809\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221521310218\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182379\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022BLN\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, BLN said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou did a mistake updating the title of the topic. We\u0027re in 2018 now \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0 \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57838-triggerau/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257838\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57838-triggerau/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@TriggerAu\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThanks for the update !\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn march the 17th...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"BLN","CreatedById":182379,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-17T18:51:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223325484\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002222809\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221521310800\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022122127\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022maculator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n30 minutes ago, maculator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn march the 17th...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhoops ok \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0Haha I thought it meant 2017 !\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Technical Ben","CreatedById":10512,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-18T12:27:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you so much! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Khesperus","CreatedById":186812,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-18T16:47:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223325037\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002222809\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221521280079\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168819\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022blakemw\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 17/03/2018 at 10:47 AM, blakemw said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUsing the new version of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E in Making History, when I add alarms (i.e. transfer window) or sometimes even go\u00A0to add an alarm the mouse cursor disappears until I restart the game. Haven\u0027t had this happen without using \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E. \u003Ca href=\u0022https://pastebin.com/raw/DDAWMXxV\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EKSP.log\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0for if it is helpful.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpecifically it happens when you mouse over the scrollbar. I think this is a Unity bug, and not specific to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E, but there is probably some workaround that TriggerAu could implement.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyhow, I\u0027m satisfied that so long as I avoid the scrollbar I\u0027m in good shape.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TriggerAu","CreatedById":57838,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-18T21:57:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndarn thats a pesky one\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith the repro steps I can have a look. One of these days have to rewrite this to not use IMGUI - but its a daunting task\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee what I can find\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Khesperus","CreatedById":186812,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-19T06:19:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223326920\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002222809\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221521410277\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257838\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TriggerAu\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, TriggerAu said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndarn thats a pesky one\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith the repro steps I can have a look. One of these days have to rewrite this to not use IMGUI - but its a daunting task\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee what I can find\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo worries, no hurry. We can\u00A0all just\u00A0learn to avoid the scrollbar for now. I probably don\u0027t need an alarm for every transfer window anyway. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Khesperus","CreatedById":186812,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-19T07:46:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOops. I was wrong. It isn\u0027t the scrollbar, It\u0027s the right side window expander. Maybe that can be disabled for now?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kaa253","CreatedById":68628,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-19T13:09:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223327311\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002222809\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221521445578\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022186812\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Khesperus\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Khesperus said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOops. I was wrong. It isn\u0027t the scrollbar, It\u0027s the right side window expander. Maybe that can be disabled for now?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think you have got the correct GUI component\u00A0now, yes I agree. RHS window edge. Good job!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bkerman","CreatedById":186979,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-21T15:58:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI also have the cursor disappearing bug. It happens at the very least with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E and Toolbar Controller. It seems it happen any time the cursor changes from the default pointer. For example, when the cursor changes to \u0022resize\u0022 arrows to resize the box... when the cursor tries to change back, it simply disappears.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUbuntu 17.10 build 1.4.1.2089\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you for the help!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-03-21T16:15:47Z\u0022 title=\u002203/21/2018 04:15  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 21, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by bkerman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003ECouldn\u0026#039;t verify Remote tech caused a bug\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TriggerAu","CreatedById":57838,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-21T22:03:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHeres an interesting question for you all experiencing the cursor thing\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs anyone seeing this on Windows or OSX - all the comms Ive got on it appear to be Linux?\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/186979-bkerman/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022186979\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/186979-bkerman/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@bkerman\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0When you say \u0022Toolbar Controller\u0022 do you refer to another mod?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bkerman","CreatedById":186979,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-21T22:10:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n@TriggerAu, Yes another mod. Just trying to highlight that the bug isn\u0027t exclusive to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E. \u0022Toolbar Controller\u0022 also has a \u0022move window\u0022 feature that changes the cursor and has similar bug where the default cursor does not come back. I know you don\u0027t maintain that, but I\u0027m hoping any info helps.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DerekL1963","CreatedById":57091,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-21T22:21:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223330439\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002222809\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221521669798\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257838\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TriggerAu\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation