aid:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthanks both, be interesting to see if its platform specific and ill try and repro tonight too\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57838-triggerau/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257838\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57838-triggerau/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@TriggerAu\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0I was working with \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022129964\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@linuxgurugamer\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0on this same bug, it\u0027s related to the custom cursor loads, and appears to only affect the linux client.\u00A0 He hasn\u0027t solved it yet, but was only able to reproduce it on a linux install.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1slfwuQfhSwd_C56tknu55PkENL4m6rGN?usp=sharing\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1slfwuQfhSwd_C56tknu55PkENL4m6rGN?usp=sharing\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0is a video of it happening on toolbar.\u00A0 Notice the interaction with the 4-way cursor and then the loss of the cursor altogether.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI also use \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E and transferwindowplanner so I\u0027m keen on helping anyway you need.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-03-23T13:58:09Z\u0022 title=\u002203/23/2018 01:58  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 23, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by devoid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-23T15:25:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223330612\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002222809\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221521679185\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257838\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TriggerAu\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/21/2018 at 8:39 PM, TriggerAu said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthanks both, be interesting to see if its platform specific and ill try and repro tonight too\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI haven\u0027t yet been able to fix this.\u00A0 But it\u0027s reproducible in a Linux Xubuntu 16.04 VM under VMWare\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nlet me know if you get a solution, I had to put this aside to work on other stuff (such as KSP-AVC,etc).\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, if you need someone to test\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223330452\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002222809\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221521670256\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022186979\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022bkerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/21/2018 at 6:10 PM, bkerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n@TriggerAu, Yes another mod. Just trying to highlight that the bug isn\u0027t exclusive to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E. \u0022Toolbar Controller\u0022 also has a \u0022move window\u0022 feature that changes the cursor and has similar bug where the default cursor does not come back. I know you don\u0027t maintain that, but I\u0027m hoping any info helps.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s the Blizzy Toolbar, NOT the Toolbar Controller.\u00A0 The Toolbar Controller uses the Blizzy Toolbar\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-23T15:36:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m thinking of adding the following code to the cursor stuff in the toolbar:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Eif (Application.platform != RuntimePlatform.LinuxPlayer)\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMay be an idea for you as well\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-23T16:37:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just released an update for the Blizzy toolbar which disables the cursor switching on Linux.\u00A0 It\u0027s not great, but at least the cursor doesn\u0027t disappear now\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223330054\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002222809\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221521647910\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022186979\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022bkerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/21/2018 at 11:58 AM, bkerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI also have the cursor disappearing bug. It happens at the very least with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E and Toolbar Controller. It seems it happen any time the cursor changes from the default pointer. For example, when the cursor changes to \u0022resize\u0022 arrows to resize the box... when the cursor tries to change back, it simply disappears.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUbuntu 17.10 build 1.4.1.2089\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you for the help!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t believe that \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E has implemented the Toolbar controller yet, so that was not relevent.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TriggerAu","CreatedById":57838,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-23T21:02:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the info guys, Ill definitely look at that stuff this weekend\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TriggerAu","CreatedById":57838,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-25T10:36:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff; color:#353c41; font-size:14px; text-align:start\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#c0392b\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Ev3.9.1.0 Released\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff; color:#353c41; font-size:14px; text-align:start\u0022\u003E\nYou\u0027ll find it in all the usual places - Has some logic to not do\u00A0the custom cursors on Linux only as \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0026amp;do=hoverca